1. Definitions

“Software” means the source code, binaries, assets, and documentation
provided in this repository and any derivative works of it.

“Non-Commercial Use” means any use that is not intended for or directed
toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation. This includes
personal projects, educational use, research, tinkering, and portfolio
projects used to showcase skills, so long as you are not selling access
to the Software or a work based substantially on it, and not using it as
a direct revenue-generating component of a product or service.

“Commercial Use” means any use of the Software intended for or directed
toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation, including but not
limited to:
- Selling, licensing, or renting the Software or derivative works;
- Using the Software as part of a product, service, or game that is sold,
  monetized (including via ads, subscriptions, or in-app purchases), or
  otherwise generates revenue;
- Using the Software internally by a for-profit entity in connection with
  a commercial product or service.

